summary:
I'm working on more but I might need some help from you guys. 
On the contrary it was quite an adventure of imagination for me....
body:
I’m working on more but I might need some help from you guys.

On the contrary it was quite an adventure of imagination for me. The elite four would be paper a grass type, salt and pepper a fairy type(a double battle. I know that counts like three but shhh let me live), Pickle a bug type? And Bomb a fire type. The pokemon champion would obviously be OJ.

The the elites would be in the hotel, each floor being one of them. OJ would be at the top floor.

The gyms would be at random and tbh I am having a bit trouble with it. Test tube would be a Psychic type and you would have to go in the lab to fight her. Bow would be a ghost type gym and, you guessed it, would have to go to the haunted mansion. Light bulb would be an electric type, knife a steel, paint brush a normal (sorry no crab :*(. I was thinking about them being a fire type but nah), Trophy a fighting, Nickel a dark and baseball a ground. Idk where they’ll be. They could just be there idk.

summary: Althought I'm still waiting for the Sinnoh remakes, Sword and Shield look quite nice so far, and since I'm starting to draw more...
caption:
Althought I’m still waiting for the Sinnoh remakes, Sword and Shield look quite nice so far, and since I’m starting to draw more why not do my good boi Piplup with this lovely shy lizard.

And I’m still hoping for the remakes in this gen, specially because *puts on tin foil hat:*

Gen 2 got remakes in Gen 4 (2+2=4)

Gen 3 got remakes in Gen 6 (3+3=6)

Gen 4 has to get remakes in Gen 8 (4+4=8)

Okay I’m done. *Takes out tin foil hat.*

summary: Heyyyy! Are you excited for the new pokemon game???? What starters have you picked in the past and what are you going to pick...
question: Heyyyy! Are you excited for the new pokemon game???? What starters have you picked in the past and what are you going to pick for the new game?!?!?!?!
answer:
I am looking forward to it! In fact, I have a feeling it’s going to take up most of my free time when it’s released! I love the Pokemon games! So much, in fact, that I’ve actually caught every single one of them. Yep, I’ve caught ‘em all, along with dozens upon dozens of shinies! One of my favourite aspects is also naming my little friends. Below is a list of all the starters I’ve picked over the years and what I named them:

I named Hanzo after the historical samurai-ninja from the Sengoku era of Japan, not after the character from Overwatch. I also have a shiny greninja named Hattori, since Hattori Hanzo was his full name.

As for the new gen, I haven’t fully decided who I’m going to pick or what I’m going to name him, but I’m leaning towards scorbunny. Ultimately, it will depend on the final evolution, but if everything works out I’ll either name him Pipkin or Vervain (based on the rabbits from Watership Down), depending on how much his appearance intensifies. If I end up choosing sobble, I’ll probably name him Eco, and if I pick Grookey, I’ll probably name him Root.
